## Best Practices

### DO ✅

```ruby
# Use eager loading to avoid N+1
Article.includes(:user, :tags)

# Use find_each for large datasets
Article.find_each { |a| process(a) }

# Use pluck for single columns
Article.pluck(:title)

# Use exists? for existence checks
Article.exists?(slug: 'my-article')

# Index foreign keys and frequent queries
add_index :articles, :user_id
add_index :articles, :status

# Use scopes for reusable queries
scope :published, -> { where(status: 'published') }

# Select only needed columns
Article.select(:id, :title)

# Use counter cache for counts
belongs_to :user, counter_cache: true

# Use appropriate join type
joins    # Filter only
includes # Load associations
```

### DON'T ❌

```ruby
# Don't cause N+1 queries
articles = Article.all
articles.each { |a| a.user.name }  # N+1!

# Don't load all records for count
Article.all.count      # Bad
Article.count          # Good

# Don't use map when pluck works
Article.all.map(&:id)  # Bad
Article.pluck(:id)     # Good

# Don't forget indexes on foreign keys
# Always: add_index :articles, :user_id

# Don't use any? for existence checks
Article.where(slug: 'test').any?     # Bad
Article.exists?(slug: 'test')        # Good

# Don't load records unnecessarily
if Article.where(user_id: 1).any?    # Loads records
if Article.exists?(user_id: 1)       # Just checks existence

# Don't use SQL directly without sanitization
# Bad: SQL injection risk
Article.where("title = '#{params[:title]}'")
# Good: Parameterized
Article.where("title = ?", params[:title])

# Don't ignore Bullet gem warnings
# Fix N+1 queries it detects!
```

